job.name: DataStaging-mzML
job.text:
Data staging node providing the primary data (mzML) to the workflow.
IN-FILESTOSTAGE: A text file containing the absolute paths of each file in a row (paths in the openBIS DSS). This information comes from the portal.
IN-JOBNAME: The job name is used as the main folder for the workflow's temporary, log, and result files. Should be the same for all data staging nodes.
OUT-STAGEDFILES: Generator port yielding a list of the staged files.

input.name: IN-FILESTOSTAGE
input.text: IN-FILESTOSTAGE: A text file containing the absolute paths of each file in a row (paths in the openBIS DSS). This information comes from the portal.

input.name: IN-JOBNAME
input.text: IN-JOBNAME: The job name is used as the main folder for the workflow's temporary, log, and result files. Should be the same for all data staging nodes.

output.name: OUT-STAGEDFILES
output.text: OUT_STAGEDFILES: Generator port yielding a list of the staged files.

job.name: XTandemAdapter
job.text:
X!TandemAdapter from the OpenMS library (peptide ID).
IN-MZML: input mzML file(s) (with MS2 spectra) IN-CTD: X!TandemAdapter parameter file IN-FASTA: protein DB with appended decoy data
OUT-IDXML: peptide idXML file(s)

input.text: IN-MZML: input mzML file(s) (with MS2 spectra)

job.name: DataStaging-writeResults
job.text:
Data staging node writing back the results to openBIS.
IN-FILESTOSTAGE: A text file containing the absolute paths of each file in a row (paths of result files on scratch).
IN-JOBNAME: The job name is used as the main folder for the workflow's temporary, log, and result files. Should be the same for all data staging nodes.
IN-REGISTERNAME: This is the prefix of the results folder name (e.g. SPACE-PROJECT-EXPERIMENT) that is reported back to openBIS.
